    "text": "LONDON, Jan 12 (Reuters) - Troubled British engineer GKN has rejected an unsolicited offer from rival Melrose and set out plans to split its business in half as it recovers from a profit warning.\nThe offer, valuing the business at 405 pence ($5.48) per share, sent shares in GKN up 20 percent to 398 pence in early Friday trading.\n$1 = 0.7385 pounds Reporting by Kate Holton; editing by Costas Pitas\n ",
